QUICK TEST (ALWAYS DO)

curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/ingest

-H "Content-Type: application/json"
-d '{"transaction_id":"t1","source_account":"A1","destination_account":"A2","amount":100,"timestamp":123,"currency":"USD","channel":"online","country":"US","label":1}'

Then check graph-builder terminal → must show:
CONSUMER RECEIVED: {...}

NEO4J CHECK

MATCH (a:Account)
RETURN a.account_id, a.is_laundering;

ML FLOW

python ml/export.py
python ml/train_model.py

IF SOMETHING BREAKS

Kill everything
pkill -f uvicorn
pkill -f consumer
pkill -f python
Restart Docker
sudo docker restart redpanda
sudo docker restart neo4j
Restart all terminals in order

PIPELINE FLOW

Loader / curl
→ Ingestion API
→ Kafka (Redpanda)
→ Graph Builder (consumer)
→ Neo4j
→ ML

CRITICAL RULES

Kafka topic must match in both services
Always check graph-builder terminal first
Never debug from Neo4j directly
Split data before balancing in ML
Do not push dataset to GitHub

This is your complete operating manual.